description:
Products covered by this EPD satisfy general purpose concrete as used in residential, commercial and public works
applications in Dubai, UAE. This EPD reports the impacts for different ready-mixed concrete products (listed in
Table 1 on the following page) in accordance with the following:
• Dubai Municipality Circular 202: Use of Eco-friendly Cementitious Materials in Concrete
• ACI 211: Standard Practice for Selecting Proportions for Normal, Heavyweight, and Mass Concrete
• ACI 318: Building Code Requirements for Structural Concrete
• ASTM C94: Standard Specification for Ready-Mixed Concrete
• CSI MasterFormat Division 03-30-00: Cast-in-Place Concrete
• UNSPSC Code 30111500: Ready Mix Concrete

description:
Products covered by this EPD satisfy general purpose concrete as used in residential, commercial and public works
applications in the United States. Product components include (in order of greatest mass per mix): Natural and
crushed aggregates, portland cement, slag cement, admixtures, and batch water.
This EPD reports the impacts for 30 different ready-mixed concrete products produce at two different Duke City
Redi-Mix facilities in accordance with the following:
• ACI 211: Standard Practice for Selecting Proportions for Normal, Heavyweight, and Mass Concrete
• ACI 318: Building Code Requirements for Structural Concrete
• ASTM C94: Standard Specification for Ready-Mixed Concrete
• CSI MasterFormat Division 03-30-00: Cast-in-Place Concrete
• UNSPSC Code 30111500: Ready Mix

description: The current assessment has been carried out by General Beton Romania in order to evaluate the environmental impact of its main product, the ready-mix concrete. It is manufactured in plastic state and subsequently delivered on construction sites to create building elements (that could have structural or non-structural functions) or infrastructure elements (i.e. roads, bridges etc.). The ready-mix concrete is manufactured in the Romanian plants owned by General Beton Romania according to the following standards and norms: EN 206:2013+A1:2016 Concrete - Part 1 transposed into Romanian Standard SR EN 206-1: 2014; SR EN 206-1 transposed into Romanian Standard SR 13510:2006/C91:2008; CP NE 012/1-2007; NE 014-2002.
